HEADWORD: Ripper bill
<hw>Rip"per bill</hw> }</mhw>.
<def>An act or a bill conferring upon a chief executive, as a governor
or mayor, large powers of appointment and removal of heads of
departments or other subordinate officials.</def> <mark>[Polit. Cant, U.
S.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

